🛠️ Task 1 – Create Advanced Workflow

Create:

mkdir -p .github/workflows
nano .github/workflows/advanced-ci.yml

Add:

name: Advanced CI Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

  pull_request:
    branches:
      - main

  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:

  lint:
    name: Validate Bash Scripts
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install ShellCheck
        run: |
          sudo apt-get update
          sudo apt-get install -y shellcheck

      - name: Run ShellCheck
        run: |
          shellcheck app/*.sh


  test:
    name: Run Tests
    needs: lint
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Make Scripts Executable
        run: chmod +x app/*.sh

      - name: Run Tests
        run: ./app/test.sh


  build:
    name: Build Application
    needs: test
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Create Build
        run: |
          mkdir -p build
          cp app/app.sh build/
          cp app/test.sh build/

      - name: Upload Build Artifact
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: application-build
          path: build/
🔗 Understanding needs

This:

needs: lint

means:

lint
 ↓
test
 ↓
build

If the lint job fails:

lint ❌
   ↓
test ⏭️ skipped
   ↓
build ⏭️ skipped

This is called job dependency.

🛠️ Task 2 – Add Matrix Strategy

Create a new job:

  compatibility:
    name: Test on Multiple Ubuntu Versions
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    strategy:
      matrix:
        shell:
          - bash

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Check Bash Version
        run: |
          bash --version

Matrix builds are useful when testing applications against multiple versions or environments.

🛠️ Task 3 – Add Scheduled Execution

Update the workflow:

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

  pull_request:
    branches:
      - main

  workflow_dispatch:

  schedule:
    - cron: "0 0 * * *"

This runs the workflow daily.

⚠️ GitHub Actions uses UTC time for cron schedules.

